While the above example leads in the right direction, I found that the `inputRef` contains the `input` element itself, so there is no need for further selectors to get to it.
Also, no need to explicitly check if the `inputRef.current` has a value or not; check below:  

```ts
const MyComponent = () => {
 const inputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);

 useEffect(() => {
    inputRef.current?.focus();
  }, []);

  return (
      <TextField
        inputRef={inputRef}
        // ....
      />
  )
}
```

